load ../settle-stopping.maude

--- The corruption pattern throughout: a certificate minted below the
--- evidence threshold -- the run-until-N ritual's lucky streak wearing an
--- anytime-valid guarantee it never earned.

--- Bite: a stream whose contrary evidence keeps the level below K never
--- certifies under the sound rule, in any interleaving.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SETTLE-STOPPING :
  sound open level(z) thresh(s(s(s(z)))) stream(strong ; contrary ; strong ; contrary ; nilO)
  =>* certified RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Hazard demonstrated: the naive point-estimate certifier mints a
--- certificate from the very same stream on the first lucky pass.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SETTLE-STOPPING :
  naive open passes(z) stream(strong ; contrary ; strong ; contrary ; nilO)
  =>* certified RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: sustained evidence crosses the threshold and certifies --
--- and the crossing needs no exhaustion (anytime validity).
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SETTLE-STOPPING :
  sound open level(z) thresh(s(s(s(z)))) stream(strong ; strong ; strong ; strong ; nilO)
  =>* certified RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: exhaustion below the threshold is an honest undetermined.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SETTLE-STOPPING :
  sound open level(z) thresh(s(s(s(z)))) stream(strong ; contrary ; nilO)
  =>* undetermined RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: undetermined and certified are mutually exclusive outcomes of
--- one settle -- an exhausted-below-K stream cannot also certify.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-SETTLE-STOPPING :
  sound open level(z) thresh(s(s(s(z)))) stream(strong ; contrary ; nilO)
  =>* certified undetermined RESIDUAL:Cfg .
